# Privacy Policy – CSV Studio

*Last updated: March 2026*

CSV Studio is developed by Lindborg. This privacy policy explains what information the app accesses and how it is handled.

---

## Data Collection

CSV Studio does **not** collect, store, or transmit any personal data. No analytics, crash reporting, or tracking of any kind is included in the app.

## Your Files

Files you open or import are read and processed entirely on your device. No file content is ever uploaded to any server or shared with any third party. CSV Studio only accesses files that you explicitly open or drag into the app.

## iCloud

If you choose to save documents to iCloud Drive, those files are synced between your own devices via Apple's iCloud infrastructure. This sync is governed by [Apple's Privacy Policy](https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/). CSV Studio has no access to iCloud data other than the documents you explicitly save there.

## Preferences

App settings such as your selected theme are stored locally on your device using macOS's standard UserDefaults mechanism. This data never leaves your device.

## Third-Party Services

CSV Studio does not use any third-party SDKs, advertising networks, or analytics services.

## Children's Privacy

The app does not collect any information from anyone, including children under the age of 13.

## Changes to This Policy

If this policy changes, the updated version will be published at this URL with a revised date at the top.

